===============================================================================
                          GETTING STARTED WITH AETHERMUD
===============================================================================

Welcome to AetherMUD, a Rifts-based multi-user dungeon!

FIRST STEPS:
------------
1. Read through character creation carefully
2. Choose from 51 races (type 'help races' for list)
3. Select from 36 Occupational Character Classes (type 'help occs')
4. Allocate your stats (IQ, ME, MA, PS, PP, PE, PB, Spd)
5. Choose your skills and abilities

BASIC COMMANDS:
--------------
  look / l          - Examine your surroundings
  inventory / i     - Check what you're carrying
  stats             - View your character statistics
  score             - See your complete character sheet
  equipment         - Show what you're wearing/wielding
  
MOVEMENT:
---------
  north / n         - Move north
  south / s         - Move south
  east / e          - Move east
  west / w          - Move west
  up / u            - Move up
  down / d          - Move down
  
  exits             - Show available exits

COMMUNICATION:
--------------
  say <message>     - Speak (others in room hear you)
  chat <message>    - Out-of-character global chat
  whisper <person> <message> - Whisper to someone
  introduce <name>  - Introduce yourself to someone
  remember <person> - See who someone is after introduction
  forget <person>   - Forget someone's identity

COMBAT:
-------
  attack <target>   - Initiate combat
  kill <target>     - Same as attack
  flee              - Attempt to escape combat

OBJECTS:
--------
  get <item>        - Pick up an item
  drop <item>       - Drop an item
  give <item> <person> - Give item to someone
  wear <armor>      - Wear armor
  wield <weapon>    - Wield a weapon
  remove <item>     - Remove worn/wielded equipment
  unwield <weapon>  - Unwield weapon

HELP SYSTEM:
-----------
  help              - Show basic help
  help <topic>      - Get help on specific topic
  help commands     - List all commands
  help races        - List all races
  help occs         - List all OCCs

IMPORTANT CONCEPTS:
------------------
  help combat       - Combat system explanation
  help identity     - Identity/introduction system
  help skills       - Skills system
  help magic        - Magic and spells
  help psionics     - Psionic powers
  help alignment    - Alignment system

SAVING:
-------
Your character saves automatically. You can also type 'save' to force a save.

Type 'quit' or 'logout' to leave the game safely.

===============================================================================
For more information, type: help <topic>
===============================================================================
